WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.720
Number four, it was several weeks ago

00:00:01.720 --> 00:00:04.880
that I preached part one of this message.

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:06.159
And I know some folks have been wondering

00:00:06.159 --> 00:00:07.539
about when part two was gonna be.

00:00:07.539 --> 00:00:10.119
In fact, I've received a couple of text messages

00:00:10.119 --> 00:00:11.399
over the past few weeks.

00:00:11.399 --> 00:00:14.359
Is part two of that message gonna be this Sunday night?

00:00:14.359 --> 00:00:16.920
And it was no, and no, and now here we are,

00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:20.399
and it's part two, and I'm thankful for God's grace.

00:00:20.399 --> 00:00:22.879
And last year, we talked about the grace of God

00:00:22.879 --> 00:00:24.780
and God's grace is sufficient.

00:00:24.780 --> 00:00:27.319
We spoke about the fact that God's grace,

00:00:27.319 --> 00:00:31.719
His saving grace, for by grace are you saved through faith.

00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:33.360
But then we focused and we talked about

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:35.740
His serving grace, His enabling,

00:00:35.740 --> 00:00:39.080
and the grace of God that's been bestowed upon us.

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:41.680
And here in our text of scripture,

00:00:41.680 --> 00:00:43.080
he says at the end of verse number 10,

00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:46.580
as good stewards of the manifold grace of God.

00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:49.279
And we wanna be good stewards of God's grace.

00:00:49.279 --> 00:00:53.040
The Bible tells us that it's required in stewards

00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.799
that a man be found faithful.

00:00:55.799 --> 00:00:58.599
And we understand the role of a steward

00:00:58.599 --> 00:01:00.919
and the responsibility of a steward

00:01:00.919 --> 00:01:04.160
and the importance of a steward being found faithful.

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:07.360
And we wanna be good stewards of the manifold grace of God.

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:11.319
The gift that God has bestowed upon us,

00:01:11.319 --> 00:01:14.680
we wanna use for His honor and for His glory.

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:17.360
And so I titled the message, Even So Minister.

00:01:17.360 --> 00:01:19.440
We see it right in the middle of verse number 10.

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:20.959
And we looked at this again,

00:01:20.959 --> 00:01:22.519
part one was several weeks ago,

00:01:22.519 --> 00:01:24.720
but let me use, read the verses of scripture.

00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:26.459
We'll dig in this evening.

00:01:26.459 --> 00:01:28.480
In 1 Peter 4, in verse number 10,

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:32.680
the Bible says, as every man hath received the gift,

00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:36.879
even so minister the same one to another,

00:01:36.879 --> 00:01:40.779
as good stewards of the manifold grace of God.

00:01:40.779 --> 00:01:44.559
If any man speak, let him speak as the oracles of God.

00:01:44.559 --> 00:01:46.599
If any man minister, let him do it

00:01:46.599 --> 00:01:49.339
as of the ability which God giveth,

00:01:49.339 --> 00:01:52.160
that God in all things may be glorified

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:55.360
through Jesus Christ to whom be praise

00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:59.279
and dominion forever and ever, amen.

00:01:59.279 --> 00:02:02.620
And we examined several portions of scripture

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:05.260
a few weeks ago as we looked at part number one.

00:02:05.260 --> 00:02:08.199
And really what we were seeking to do in that message

00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:11.600
was to establish a foundational understanding

00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:12.919
of spiritual gifts.

00:02:12.919 --> 00:02:15.779
And here's just a quick overview of that first message.

00:02:15.779 --> 00:02:18.360
If you were not here or because of the fact

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:19.919
that it's been several weeks

00:02:19.919 --> 00:02:22.600
and I put the Sunday school class this morning,

00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:23.800
our teen Sunday school class.

00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:26.440
I said, hey, how was it last week

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:27.800
with brother Travis Campbell?

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:28.919
Oh, it was great.

00:02:28.919 --> 00:02:29.940
I said, man, that's wonderful.

00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:31.639
What did he preach on?

00:02:31.639 --> 00:02:33.520
Man, I wish I had my notes.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:34.639
Man, I wish I had my notes.

00:02:34.639 --> 00:02:36.259
Like none of them could remember.

00:02:36.259 --> 00:02:37.960
And I'm not throwing them under the bus.

00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:40.520
I'm simply saying we have so many things

00:02:40.520 --> 00:02:42.919
that happen in our lives that we kind of,

00:02:43.880 --> 00:02:45.380
and as they kind of sat there,

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:47.020
they were starting to remember certain things.

00:02:47.020 --> 00:02:48.740
And then somebody said, oh yeah, he preached on this.

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:49.899
And that was in the morning.

00:02:49.899 --> 00:02:50.740
No, no, no.

00:02:50.740 --> 00:02:51.580
Somebody else, no, no.

00:02:51.580 --> 00:02:52.399
That was in the evening.

00:02:52.399 --> 00:02:53.240
And somebody else, no, no.

00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:54.080
And it was just kind of,

00:02:54.080 --> 00:02:55.740
and that's how we are as humans, right?

00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:57.860
We just, we need to be reminded of some things.

00:02:57.860 --> 00:03:00.580
And so we noted several things

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:03.679
that I think it's important that we rehearse this evening

00:03:03.679 --> 00:03:05.240
as we go into part number two.

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:06.759
The first thing that we noted is this,

00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:08.500
and we see it in verse number 10.

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:11.380
And that is that every believer

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:13.559
has been given a spiritual gift.

00:03:13.559 --> 00:03:17.380
It says, as every man hath received the gift.

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:19.940
The gift here in 1 Peter 4 and verse number 10

00:03:19.940 --> 00:03:21.779
is not the gift of salvation,

00:03:21.779 --> 00:03:24.919
although salvation is the greatest gift

00:03:24.919 --> 00:03:27.139
that any of us could ever receive.

00:03:27.139 --> 00:03:29.220
It's the greatest gift that we possess.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:32.440
The reality is that here, contextually,

00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:35.259
he's not talking about the gift of salvation.

00:03:35.259 --> 00:03:37.559
He's talking about spiritual gifts.

00:03:37.559 --> 00:03:40.720
And he says, as every man hath received the gift.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:43.740
And this is, the word man is referring to mankind,

00:03:43.740 --> 00:03:44.839
every child of God.

00:03:44.839 --> 00:03:47.399
It's not talking about the lost having received a gift.

00:03:47.399 --> 00:03:49.800
It's talking about the people of God.

00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:51.679
And so if you're here and you've been saved

00:03:51.679 --> 00:03:53.279
by the grace of God,

00:03:53.279 --> 00:03:56.720
you have been given a spiritual gift.

00:03:56.720 --> 00:03:59.679
We also understood, and we focused on the fact

00:03:59.679 --> 00:04:02.440
that it's the Holy Spirit who gives

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:05.259
to every man as he wills.

00:04:05.259 --> 00:04:08.199
In other words, it's not that it's a buffet type

00:04:08.199 --> 00:04:10.479
of a situation where we look down the line and say,

00:04:10.479 --> 00:04:13.399
okay, here are the spiritual gifts that are available.

00:04:13.399 --> 00:04:16.359
And I think this is the line that I'm going to get into

00:04:16.359 --> 00:04:18.339
because this is the one that I'd really like.

00:04:18.339 --> 00:04:22.600
No, the Holy Spirit of God giveth to every man

00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:24.760
severally as he will.

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:27.600
And he doeth all things well, amen.

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:28.839
God doeth all things well.

00:04:28.839 --> 00:04:30.299
The Holy Spirit is God.

00:04:30.299 --> 00:04:33.220
And we know that as we understand the spiritual gifts

00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:36.600
and the Holy Spirit, the Holy Ghost will give

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:38.000
that spiritual gift.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:40.000
And it's appropriate, it's right.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:41.200
It's not a situation where we say,

00:04:41.200 --> 00:04:42.880
well, that's not the one I wanted.

00:04:43.320 --> 00:04:44.920
No, God knows better than you do.

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:46.600
He knows better than I do.

00:04:46.600 --> 00:04:48.799
And he gives the spiritual gifts

00:04:48.799 --> 00:04:51.720
and he talks about the church being a body.

00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:55.600
And as the body is joined together,

00:04:55.600 --> 00:04:58.000
fitly joined together, and we find that as God

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.239
would equip his saints with the spiritual gifts,

00:05:01.239 --> 00:05:04.579
that the body of Christ, as we use our spiritual gifts,

00:05:04.579 --> 00:05:08.579
we bring glory to God as everyone is using the gift

00:05:08.579 --> 00:05:10.480
that's been given to them.

00:05:10.480 --> 00:05:12.239
One of the problems in the church in Corinth,

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:13.959
when I was having this conversation,

00:05:13.959 --> 00:05:15.980
it's always interesting as a guest speaker,

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:18.480
I got done preaching last Sunday there in Hawaii

00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:21.079
and I got done and several people,

00:05:21.079 --> 00:05:23.040
they wanna talk to you and give you comments

00:05:23.040 --> 00:05:24.920
about whatever, they appreciate the message,

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:25.799
so on and so forth.

00:05:25.799 --> 00:05:29.920
And it was a real blessing to just kinda be used

00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:32.440
of the Lord to be a blessing to those folks there.

00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:33.839
And then you always can kinda tell

00:05:33.839 --> 00:05:35.160
when somebody really wants to talk to you

00:05:35.160 --> 00:05:36.239
a little bit more.

00:05:36.239 --> 00:05:38.679
And this one person wanted to talk to me a little bit more

00:05:38.679 --> 00:05:40.339
and I knew as soon as they started talking,

00:05:40.339 --> 00:05:42.619
I need to make sure I find a way, a gap,

00:05:42.619 --> 00:05:44.720
to be able to say, you need to talk to your pastor.

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:45.559
Why?

00:05:45.559 --> 00:05:46.779
Because I'm not their pastor, amen?

00:05:46.779 --> 00:05:49.500
I am a pastor, but I was not their pastor.

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:51.459
And the things that they were sharing with me,

00:05:51.459 --> 00:05:54.260
they needed to be able to talk to their pastor.

00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:55.579
And some of the things that they were sharing,

00:05:55.579 --> 00:05:58.220
I then talked to the pastor, gave him a heads up,

00:05:58.220 --> 00:06:00.019
hey, somebody came to me and here's what they talked

00:06:00.019 --> 00:06:02.019
to me about, and I just wanted to let you know

00:06:02.019 --> 00:06:06.059
that I pointed them to you and give you a heads up.

00:06:06.059 --> 00:06:08.019
And they're like, well, why didn't you fix the problem?

00:06:08.019 --> 00:06:10.100
Because that's not my job, amen?

00:06:10.859 --> 00:06:13.179
And the reality is that one thing that I told him

00:06:13.179 --> 00:06:15.899
to try to encourage him is that oftentimes

00:06:15.899 --> 00:06:17.179
when we look at the church in Corinth,

00:06:17.179 --> 00:06:19.540
it's the most carnal church in the New Testament.

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:22.359
It's a church that's being corrected for its error

00:06:22.359 --> 00:06:24.220
with regard to spiritual gifts,

00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:26.339
but yet oftentimes people want to run

00:06:26.339 --> 00:06:28.019
to the book of First Corinthians

00:06:28.019 --> 00:06:31.739
and withdraw certain portions of scripture

00:06:31.739 --> 00:06:35.619
and set up teaching and doctrine that's erroneous.

00:06:35.619 --> 00:06:37.540
And you're dealing with a carnal church

00:06:37.540 --> 00:06:40.940
that's being corrected for their wrongdoing,

00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:42.739
and you're gonna try to build doctrine on it.

00:06:42.739 --> 00:06:44.579
It's a terrible mistake.

00:06:44.579 --> 00:06:47.739
And so we find that the Holy Spirit

00:06:47.739 --> 00:06:49.500
gives to every man as he wills.

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.140
And here's the thing, what happens

00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:52.540
and what was happening in Corinth

00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:55.179
is people were saying, well, I want that spiritual gift.

00:06:55.179 --> 00:06:57.380
They were coveting after certain spiritual gifts.

00:06:57.380 --> 00:07:00.420
The one that was kind of on the top of the list was tongues.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:04.380
And you saw that there was absolutely a pride element

00:07:04.420 --> 00:07:07.619
with regard to that, which is still prevalent today

00:07:07.619 --> 00:07:09.779
within the modern day tongues movement.

00:07:09.779 --> 00:07:12.940
And so we find that it's not that we would covet

00:07:12.940 --> 00:07:15.100
some other gift that someone else has,

00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:17.299
it is that we would understand

00:07:17.299 --> 00:07:20.299
that the Holy Spirit of God has equipped me,

00:07:20.299 --> 00:07:22.940
has given to me a spiritual gift

00:07:22.940 --> 00:07:25.980
that is the right spiritual gift for me.

00:07:25.980 --> 00:07:28.779
And so we find that we dealt with that last week.

00:07:28.779 --> 00:07:30.859
We noted that the purpose of spiritual gifts,

00:07:30.859 --> 00:07:33.059
really twofold purpose is this.

00:07:33.059 --> 00:07:36.700
Number one and primary is to glorify God.

00:07:36.700 --> 00:07:39.940
Here in 1 Peter chapter four and verse number 11,

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:42.179
it says, I'll just pick it up in the middle of the text

00:07:42.179 --> 00:07:45.739
that God in all things may be glorified

00:07:45.739 --> 00:07:47.980
through Jesus Christ to whom be praise

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:51.779
and dominion forever and ever, amen.

00:07:51.779 --> 00:07:54.859
And so the primary purpose of spiritual gifts

00:07:54.859 --> 00:07:57.179
is so that God would be glorified.

00:07:57.179 --> 00:08:00.359
We understand that John the Baptist said he must increase,

00:08:00.359 --> 00:08:01.299
I must decrease.

00:08:01.299 --> 00:08:06.299
It's all about us as his people bringing glory to his name.

00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:09.459
Whether therefore you eat or drink or whatsoever you do,

00:08:09.459 --> 00:08:12.179
do all to the glory of God.

00:08:12.179 --> 00:08:16.220
And as we minister, as we use that spiritual gift

00:08:16.220 --> 00:08:17.820
that God has equipped us with,

00:08:17.820 --> 00:08:19.820
it is to bring glory to God.

00:08:19.820 --> 00:08:22.859
Not so that we could say, look at me, look at what I know.

00:08:22.859 --> 00:08:25.579
We recognize it was God that gave it to us.

00:08:25.579 --> 00:08:28.940
I have no ability aside from God's grace

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:30.779
being bestowed upon me.

00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:33.820
And so we find that not only is the primary purpose

00:08:33.820 --> 00:08:35.859
to glorify God, but secondarily,

00:08:35.859 --> 00:08:39.739
the purpose of spiritual gifts is to edify the believers,

00:08:39.739 --> 00:08:41.799
to build up the brethren.

00:08:41.799 --> 00:08:43.340
The Bible says here in verse number 11,

00:08:43.340 --> 00:08:45.739
if any man speak, let him speak as the oracles of God.

00:08:45.739 --> 00:08:47.020
If any man minister, notice,

00:08:47.020 --> 00:08:49.419
let him do it as of the ability which God giveth.

00:08:49.419 --> 00:08:50.619
In verse number 10, it says,

00:08:50.619 --> 00:08:55.619
even so minister, notice, the same one to another.

00:08:55.960 --> 00:08:57.539
Throughout the portion of scripture

00:08:57.539 --> 00:08:58.900
in the book of 1 Corinthians

00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:01.859
as it deals with the subject of spiritual gifts,

00:09:01.859 --> 00:09:04.419
you read chapters 12, 13, and 14.

00:09:04.419 --> 00:09:05.780
And those three chapters,

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:08.880
and we looked at several verses last time

00:09:08.880 --> 00:09:10.580
with regard to the spiritual gifts

00:09:10.580 --> 00:09:12.659
there in the book of 1 Corinthians.

00:09:12.659 --> 00:09:16.340
And we find that Paul repeatedly spoke to them

00:09:16.340 --> 00:09:18.700
about edifying the brethren,

00:09:18.700 --> 00:09:21.219
building them up and encouraging them.

00:09:21.219 --> 00:09:23.700
And what an important role.

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:26.119
We understand that as we gather together,

00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:29.280
when you think about the truth of church,

00:09:29.280 --> 00:09:33.359
and yes, even as I mentioned during announcements

00:09:33.359 --> 00:09:35.460
about some folks that haven't been able to be here

00:09:35.460 --> 00:09:38.359
and have said, it's just not the same on live stream.

00:09:38.359 --> 00:09:40.099
Listen, there are things,

00:09:40.099 --> 00:09:41.919
this was a huge problem during COVID.

00:09:41.919 --> 00:09:44.419
There are things, there are commands

00:09:44.419 --> 00:09:49.419
that you and I cannot obey if we do not assemble.

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:50.780
Just impossible.

00:09:50.780 --> 00:09:52.239
In Hebrews 10 in verse 25,

00:09:52.239 --> 00:09:54.460
not forsaking the assembling of ourselves together

00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:55.640
as the manner of some is,

00:09:55.640 --> 00:10:01.159
but exhorting one another even so much more as you see.

00:10:01.159 --> 00:10:04.559
see the day approaching, he said in verse number 24,

00:10:04.559 --> 00:10:07.919
and let us consider one another to provoke unto love

00:10:07.919 --> 00:10:08.759
and to good works.

00:10:08.759 --> 00:10:12.519
These are things that we do as we assemble, as we gather.

00:10:12.519 --> 00:10:15.639
These are things that as I use my spiritual gift,

00:10:15.639 --> 00:10:17.279
as you use your spiritual gift,

00:10:17.279 --> 00:10:20.639
we're edifying the brethren.

00:10:20.639 --> 00:10:24.279
We defined the spiritual gifts as they're listed there

00:10:24.279 --> 00:10:25.919
in Romans chapter number 12.

00:10:25.919 --> 00:10:28.559
So that's kind of a quick overview of what we looked at

00:10:28.559 --> 00:10:32.359
in part number one of this even so minister

00:10:32.359 --> 00:10:36.859
and understanding how that spiritual gifts were defined

00:10:36.859 --> 00:10:37.839
in the scriptures.

00:10:37.839 --> 00:10:39.759
Now, as we make some application

00:10:39.759 --> 00:10:42.199
and really kind of deal here with part two,

00:10:42.199 --> 00:10:44.359
if you're taking notes, I would say number one,

00:10:44.359 --> 00:10:47.559
discovering your spiritual gift.

00:10:47.559 --> 00:10:49.719
And so here's the question that we have

00:10:49.719 --> 00:10:52.739
as we look at the truth that God gives us

00:10:52.739 --> 00:10:55.599
in Romans chapter number 12 with regard

00:10:55.599 --> 00:11:00.599
to the spiritual gifts and the fact that he's given

00:11:00.679 --> 00:11:02.559
to us a spiritual gift.

00:11:02.559 --> 00:11:04.599
And we looked at the gift of prophecy,

00:11:04.599 --> 00:11:06.499
the gift of ministry, the gift of teaching,

00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:08.819
the gift of exhortation, the gift of giving,

00:11:08.819 --> 00:11:10.279
of ruling and of mercy.

00:11:10.279 --> 00:11:12.639
And we looked at those gifts and we dealt with,

00:11:12.639 --> 00:11:14.399
explained each one of them.

00:11:14.399 --> 00:11:16.039
And so when you begin to say, okay,

00:11:16.039 --> 00:11:17.919
there's seven spiritual gifts,

00:11:17.919 --> 00:11:20.559
according to Romans 12, verses three through eight,

00:11:20.559 --> 00:11:24.559
how do I determine, how do I discover my spiritual gift?

00:11:24.559 --> 00:11:29.519
If God has told me in his word that I have a spiritual gift,

00:11:29.519 --> 00:11:32.359
if God has told me, and he has,

00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:34.519
that he's given to every man

00:11:34.519 --> 00:11:36.879
as every man hath received the gift,

00:11:36.879 --> 00:11:40.919
then it becomes a responsibility of the individual

00:11:40.919 --> 00:11:43.419
to discover what is my spiritual gift?

00:11:45.359 --> 00:11:46.599
Let me say this.

00:11:46.599 --> 00:11:48.959
If you don't know what your spiritual gift is,

